  "texts": [
    "But why go so far from the action theoretic mainstream?",
    "Couldn't a reformulated version of the standard story jettison the strict bodily constraint while holding onto the more intuitive elements of Davidson's model?",
    "13 Three considerations tell against this approach.",
    "First it is unclear that the Strict Bodily Constraint is inessential to the standard story.",
    "As Ford (2018) notes, the Davidsonian emphasis on finding the physical event that constitutes the agent's intentional action has a tendency to impel body-bound, \"corporalist\", or internalising, \"volitionalist\" (see, e.g., Hornsby, 1980) views of the structure of human agency."
  ],
